Package it.polimi.ingsw.server.model.mvevents.actionevents

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActionEvent
    prototype of every event that the model create to notify the view of a change in its status
    BooleanRequestEvent
    it's a boolean event and it's used for boolean request
    BuildBlockEvent
    event that is generated when block is build and also has the function creating his eventbean
    BuildDomePromptEvent
    used for the choice of build dome prompt
    BuildOrMoveEvent
    it's a boolean event and ask if you would build or move
    Coordinates
    instead of using cells for describing a position on the board Coordinates call is more useful and easy to parse
    DoubleBuildEvent
    event that is generated when a player do the double build
    DoubleMoveEvent
    event that is generated when a player do the double move
    FailedActionEvent
    event that is generated when a action fail and also has the function of creating his EventBean
    NoUpdatesEvent
    nothing more than no update
    PlayerLostEvent
    event that is generated when a player loses and also has the function of creating his eventbean
    PlayerWonEvent
    event that is generated when a player won and also has the function of creating his eventbean
    WaitingForActionEvent
    is the event that corresponds to waiting for user action and is created the eventBean
    WorkerMovementEvent
    event that is generated when a worker do a movement and also has the function of creating his eventbean
    WorkerSelectionEvent
    event that is generated when a player do a select and also has the function of creating his eventbean
